title: Plan for modifying gun triggers to go to standby on all beamcode 2 shots (to make 110, 90, and 60 Hz HXR only more tolerable)
text: Because we'll be above the ACM limits if we run four bunches at full charge and 120 Hz, we want to run at an intermediate rate like 90 Hz. Unfortunately, the EVG doesn't have any patterns to do HXR 90 with SXR 0. If we choose a pattern like HXR 90/SXR 30, then take away the MPS Gun SXR permit, it almost works, but because the MPS and EVG aren't synced up quite right, you get a lot of blocked HXR shots too. One way to mitigate this is to avoid using the MPS to shut the gun off, and instead reconfigure the gun to go to standby on all SXR (beamcode 2) pulses. We need to do two things to accomplish this: 1) Change the event code used for Gun PAC Acc triggers. We have used one of the 'user defined' event codes (133) that is a clone of the normal Klys Accel (151), except it also had a condition to only fire on beamcode 1. We will reconfigure the "RFGunPAC(20-6)Acc" trigger to use event code 133 instead of 151. (To get to this: Event/IN20 -> LLRF -> LLRF Triggers IN20:RF03 -> TTB/FP 2 Trig) 2) Change the gun modulator PDU trigger rules to deactivate the station on any beamcode 2 pulse. For this, we'll modify the "BC2 No MPS GunPAC" rule so that it evaulates to "true" for any beamcode 2 pulse. This basically just means removing the 'MPS_POCKCELL' exclusion mask that is in there now. (To get to this: Event/Global -> PDU Global Rules) We haven't implemented this yet - waiting for the 4-bunch team to finish their initial setup.

title: Implemented gun-on-beamcode-1-only scheme.
text: One 'gotcha' we discovered is that if you take away all masks on a PDU global rule, it doesn't let you use that rule to deactivate a modulator. So, we added a BKRCUS inclusion mask to the BC2 No MPS GunPAC (in addition to removing MPS_POCKCELL). The BKRCUS bit is present for every beamcode 2 pulse, so this is basically the same as a beamcode 2 filter with no masks at all. To back this out: 1) Change the RFGunPAC(20-6)Acc trigger in EVR:IN20:RF03 to use event code 151 instead of 133. 2) Change the BC2 No MPS GunPAC global PDU rule to exclude MPS_POCKCELL, and remove all inclusion masks.
